label: partOf
comment: Relates a (functional) part to its Collection. Can be implemented with dedicated #Tags

label: elementOf
comment: Relates an Element to its Set. Can be implemented with dedicated #Tags

label: instanceOf
comment: Relates an Object to its Class. Can be implemented with dedicated #Tags

label: subclassOf
comment: Relates a subclass to its super-class. Can be implemented with dedicated #Tags

label: inverseOf
comment: Relates a property to a property that is its inverse. Inverse properties relate the same pairs of items to each other, but in reversed direction. For example, the 'alumni' and 'alumniOf' properties are inverseOf each other. Some properties don't have explicit inverses; in these situations RDFa and JSON-LD syntax for reverse properties can be used.

label: isAccessoryOrSparePartFor
comment: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is an accessory or spare part.

label: appliesToDeliveryMethod
comment: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.

label: appliesToPaymentMethod
comment: The payment method(s) to which the payment charge specification applies.

label: availableIn
comment: The location in which the strength is available.

label: isBasedOn
comment: A resource from which this work is derived or from which it is a modification or adaption.

label: isBasedOnUrl
comment: A resource that was used in the creation of this resource. This term can be repeated for multiple sources. For example, http://example.com/great-multiplication-intro.html.

label: isConsumableFor
comment: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is a consumable.

label: isEncodedByBioChemEntity
comment: Another BioChemEntity encoding by this one.

label: encodesBioChemEntity
comment: Another BioChemEntity encoded by this one.

label: encodesCreativeWork
comment: The CreativeWork encoded by this media object.

label: estimatesRiskOf
comment: The condition, complication, or symptom whose risk is being estimated.

label: holdingArchive
comment: ArchiveOrganization that holds, keeps or maintains the ArchiveComponent.

domainIncludes: BroadcastService, CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event, LinkRole, PronounceableText, WriteAction
label: inLanguage
comment: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also availableLanguage.

label: includedInHealthInsurancePlan
comment: The insurance plans that cover this drug.

label: includesAttraction
comment: Attraction located at destination.

label: includesHealthPlanFormulary
comment: Formularies covered by this plan.

label: includesHealthPlanNetwork
comment: Networks covered by this plan.

label: includesObject
comment: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in an Offer or ProductCollection.

label: increasesRiskOf
comment: The condition, complication, etc. influenced by this factor.

label: isInvolvedInBiologicalProcess
comment: Biological process this BioChemEntity is involved in; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

label: isLocatedInSubcellularLocation
comment: Subcellular location where this BioChemEntity is located; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

label: makesOffer
comment: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

label: originatesFrom
comment: The vasculature the lymphatic structure originates, or afferents, from.

label: isPartOf
comment: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense), is part of.

label: isPartOfBioChemEntity
comment: Indicates a BioChemEntity that is (in some sense) a part of this BioChemEntity.

label: isPlanForApartment
comment: Indicates some accommodation that this floor plan describes.

label: providesBroadcastService
comment: The BroadcastService offered on this channel.

label: providesService
comment: The service provided by this channel.

label: publishedOn
comment: A broadcast service associated with the publication event.

label: referencesOrder
comment: The Order(s) related to this Invoice. One or more Orders may be combined into a single Invoice.

label: isRelatedTo
comment: A pointer to another, somehow related product (or multiple products).

label: runsTo
comment: The vasculature the lymphatic structure runs, or efferents, to.

label: isSimilarTo
comment: A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).

label: usesDevice
comment: Device used to perform the test.

label: isVariantOf
comment: Indicates the kind of product that this is a variant of. In the case of ProductModel, this is a pointer (from a ProductModel) to a base product from which this product is a variant. It is safe to infer that the variant inherits all product features from the base model, unless defined locally. This is not transitive. In the case of a ProductGroup, the group description also serves as a template, representing a set of Products that vary on explicitly defined, specific dimensions only (so it defines both a set of variants, as well as which values distinguish amongst those variants). When used with ProductGroup, this property can apply to any Product included in the group.

label: variesBy
comment: Indicates the property or properties by which the variants in a ProductGroup vary, e.g. their size, color etc. Schema.org properties can be referenced by their short name e.g. "color"; terms defined elsewhere can be referenced with their URIs.

label: validIn
comment: The geographic area where a permit or similar thing is valid.
